A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Civil Actions – Consumer Contracts – Limitations Periods
3 FOR the purpose of establishing that any provision of a consumer contract that sets a
4 shorter period of time to bring an action on or under the contract than otherwise
5 required under State law at the time the contract is issued or delivered is void;
6 providing that a violation of this Act is considered a violation of the Consumer
7 Protection Act; and generally relating to consumer contracts.
